Tap to share Notes: \n\n1.To use WeChat sharing, the developer must manually create the WXEntryActivity class. Otherwise, the callback of the sharing will not be received on the client.\n2. The size of the image used for WeChat sharing should be no more than 32 KB. Otherwise, the default Alipay icon will be used.\n3.To use QQ or QZone sharing, set a correct QQ sharing ID, and register it to the AndroidManifest class. Otherwise, the sharing and callback feature will fail to work properly.\n4. To use Weibo sharing, ensure that your application signature, package name, and sharing ID are consistent with that are registered on the Weibo Open Platform. Otherwise, the sharing will fail.\n5.If the SMS page is opened when you use the SMS sharing, the sharing callback succeeds. If you want to call back the sending status of the message, apply for a permission for development purposes.\n\nTap the following buttons to obtain the detailed instruction. Tap to obtain detailed instruction Alipay WeChat contacts WeChat moments Weibo QQ contacts QZone DingTalk SMS Sharing succeeded Sharing cancelled Sharing failed
